        <updateDate>2016-06-20T13:49:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Layoff Prevention Extension Act of </b> <b>2016</b></p> <p> This bill amends the Middle Class Tax Relief and Job Creation Act of 2012 with respect to state short-time compensation programs that allow employers to reduce the workweek of their employees in lieu of layoffs. The bill: (1) extends federal financing of the programs for an additional two years; and (2) extends through December 31, 2016, the deadline for a state to submit to the Department of Labor its application for a short-time compensation program grant.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
